    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bowling game played on a standard tenpin lane but with slender, cylindrical pins about 15 inches tall and tapered at both ends. The ball is 4.5 inches in diameter and weighing 2 pounds, 7 ounces. Three balls are bowled in a frame but knocked down pins are not removed until the frame is completed. </Note_Text>
